c-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\n./forge/docs/fix-java-run-fail.md:254:[dynamic-access workflow](../docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md) per-class\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:98:  [--keep-tests-without-dynamic-access] \\\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:123:- `--keep-tests-without-dynamic-access` keeps generated tests for dynamic-access workflows even if no dynamic-access call sites are covered.\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:383:coordinates, active dynamic-access classes, source-context paths, and Gradle\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:416:### Dynamic-access iterative workflow\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:418:The `dynamic_access_iterative` workflow improves metadata accuracy by using the `generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport` Gradle task to identify which dynamic-access call sites (reflection, JNI, resources, serialization) are not yet covered by the generated tests. Instead of generating tests blindly, the workflow iterates class-by-class, sending the agent targeted prompts with the exact uncovered call sites for each class. After each attempt, the report is regenerated and coverage deltas are computed to decide whether to retry the same class or move on.\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:424:Dynamic-access strategies can optionally download library source code, upstream tests, and/or documentation as read-only agent context. This is configured per strategy via the `source-context-types` parameter in `predefined_strategies.json`. Available types are `main`, `test`, and `documentation`. The artifacts are downloaded from URLs in the library's `index.json` (populated by the `populateArtifactURLs` Gradle task) and extracted to `local_repositories/source_context/<group>/<artifact>/<version>/`.\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:449:Composite strategies (run a primary workflow, then refine dynamic-access coverage):\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:456:#### Running a dynamic-access strategy\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:478:For the detailed function-level notes and sequence diagram, see `docs/dynamic-access-strategy.md`.\n./forge/docs/architecture.md:214:| `dynamic_access_iterative` | [dynamic_access_iterative_strategy.py](../ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/dynamic_access_iterative_strategy.py) | Coverage-driven loop using the dynamic-access report; targets uncovered call sites. |\n./forge/docs/architecture.md:215:| `optimistic_dynamic_access` | [optimistic_dynamic_access_strategy.py](../ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/optimistic_dynamic_access_strategy.py) | Variant of dynamic-access that primes coverage from source analysis. |\n./forge/docs/architecture.md:252:| `dynamic_access_report` | Parse `dynamic-access-coverage.json`, compute deltas, format prompts. |\n./forge/docs/architecture.md:284:  recovery, dynamic-access iteration, javac/java-run failure prompts).\n./forge/docs/functional-spec.md:21:2. **Coverage improvement** — increase dynamic-access coverage of\n./forge/docs/functional-spec.md:33:   dynamic-access coverage of already-supported libraries.\n./forge/docs/functional-spec.md:53:| **Dynamic-access report** | JSON written by Gradle task `generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport` to `tests/src/<group>/<artifact>/<version>/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json`, listing classes and per-class call sites that require dynamic-access metadata, marked covered/uncovered. |\n./forge/docs/functional-spec.md:84:- `--keep-tests-without-dynamic-access` — only honored by dynamic-access\n./forge/docs/functional-spec.md:85:  strategies; see [dynamic-access-workflow.md](dynamic-access-workflow.md).\n./forge/docs/functional-spec.md:97:  `dynamic-access-iteration`).\n./forge/docs/functional-spec.md:132:  testing, dynamic-access reporting, native metadata exploration, metadata\n./forge/docs/functional-spec.md:215:For dynamic-access workflows, Forge passes the issue number and configured\n./forge/docs/functional-spec.md:217:dynamic-access report exceeds a configured class or call chunk limit, the\n./forge/docs/functional-spec.md:228:- [Dynamic access workflow](dynamic-access-workflow.md) — guided test\n./forge/docs/functional-spec.md:229:  generation driven by the dynamic-access coverage report.\n./forge/docs/functional-spec.md:238:  final recovery to Codex. Used as the per-class gate in the dynamic-access\n./forge/docs/native-metadata-exploration.md:41:> [Dynamic-access workflow](dynamic-access-workflow.md) ·\n./forge/docs/native-metadata-exploration.md:143:where `<class-key>` is a sanitized form of the dynamic-access class the\n./forge/docs/native-metadata-exploration.md:404:| Dynamic-access workflow | [dynamic-access-workflow.md](dynamic-access-workflow.md) |\n./forge/utility_scripts/large_library_progress.py:246:        \"\"\"Record aggregate dynamic-access coverage.\"\"\"\n./forge/docs/dynamic-access-strategy.md:1:# Dynamic-access strategy internals (current PR)\n./forge/docs/dynamic-access-strategy.md:9:  - `run(...)`: runs a single generation attempt. It generates the initial dynamic-access report, falls back to `BasicIterativeStrategy` only if no usable guidance exists at the start, otherwise enters the dynamic-access class iteration immediately and counts success only after metadata generation, retest, `generateLibraryStats`, and a commit for the library iteration succeed.\n./forge/docs/dynamic-access-strategy.md:10:  - `__init__(...)`: keeps the dynamic strategy config minimal by requiring only the class-specific dynamic-access prompt and dynamic-access-specific iteration limits, while providing internal defaults for the start-of-run basic fallback prompts and fallback iteration limits.\n./forge/docs/dynamic-access-strategy.md:11:  - `_run_dynamic_access_phase(...)`: uncovered-class iteration using coverage deltas from dynamic-access reports; initializes `exhausted_classes = set()` for the phase, emits targeted prompts per uncovered class, includes the current uncovered dynamic-access call-site list in every prompt, retries `./gradlew test` failures inside a bounded per-class mini-loop by sending the failing output back to the agent, clears agent context after each class attempt sequence, treats the phase as successful once any dynamic-access call site becomes covered, enforces per-class prompt-attempt limits, and fails the generation if the dynamic-access report disappears mid-phase.\n./forge/docs/dynamic-access-strategy.md:12:  - `_generate_dynamic_access_report(...)`: runs `generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport` and loads parsed report data from `dynamic-access-coverage.json`.\n./forge/docs/dynamic-access-strategy.md:59:    else Dynamic-access guidance available\n./forge/ai_workflows/improve_library_coverage.py:6:\"\"\"Workflow entry point for improving dynamic-access coverage on an existing library.\n./forge/ai_workflows/improve_library_coverage.py:9:focuses solely on generating new tests to improve dynamic-access coverage.\n./forge/ai_workflows/improve_library_coverage.py:113:        description=\"Improve dynamic-access coverage for an existing library version.\",\n./forge/ai_workflows/improve_library_coverage.py:151:        help=\"Enable resumable large-library chunking for dynamic-access workflows.\",\n./forge/docs/native-test-verification.md:7:> **See also:** [Dynamic-access workflow](dynamic-access-workflow.md) ·\n./forge/docs/native-test-verification.md:48:The gate is the per-class success criterion for the dynamic-access workflow\n./forge/docs/native-test-verification.md:63:| Output directory | Caller | Absolute staging root for this gate invocation. The caller picks a path namespaced per (library, class) for the dynamic-access caller, or per coordinate for non-class-scoped callers — same convention as [native-metadata-exploration.md §4](native-metadata-exploration.md#4-output). The gate writes JVM-agent metadata to `<output_dir>/agent`, merged trace metadata to `<output_dir>/trace`, and writes durable repository metadata only after the final native-image-utils merge succeeds. |\n./forge/docs/native-test-verification.md:265:| `dynamic_access_iterative` pe